    "content": "The 4 T's mnemonic is the gold standard for MCCQE1.<br><br>1. <b>Tone:</b> Uterine Atony (Most common - 80%).<br>2. <b>Tissue:</b> Retained Products.<br>3. <b>Trauma:</b> Lacerations.<br>4. <b>Thrombin:</b> Coagulopathy.<br><br><div style='background:#f0f9ff; border-left:5px solid var(--blue); padding:10px; border-radius:8px;'><b>⚠️ Exam Trap:</b> The first step for a <b>boggy uterus</b> is <b>Uterine Massage</b> and Oxytocin. If the uterus is <b>firm</b> but bleeding continues, the answer is <b>Trauma/Laceration</b>.</div>",
    "quiz": { "q": "What is the most common cause of PPH?", "a": "Uterine Atony." }
