    "cat": "Ethics",
    "sub": "End of Life",
    "title": "⚖️ MAID (MEDICAL ASSISTANCE IN DYING)",
    "content": "Specific to Canadian law. Two clinicians must confirm eligibility.<br><br>• <b>Criteria:</b> 18+ years, capable of decision, grievous and irremediable medical condition.<br>• <b>Process:</b> Must be informed of <b>palliative care</b> options first.<br><br><div style='background:#fffbeb; border-left:5px solid var(--gold); padding:10px; border-radius:8px;'><b>⚠️ Exam Trap:</b> You cannot suggest MAID to a patient out of the blue. The patient must <b>initiate</b> the request. Also, clinicians have the right to <b>conscientious objection</b> but must provide a 'formal referral' in many provinces.</div>",
    "quiz": { "q": "Can a person request MAID through an advance directive in Canada currently?", "a": "No, the patient must have capacity at the time of the request (current law)." }
  },
  {
    "id": "HY-RES-24",
