    "title": "⚖️ INFORMED CONSENT",
    "content": "Consent must be voluntary, capable, specific, and informed.<br><br>• <b>Disclosure:</b> You must disclose what a 'reasonable person' in the patient's position would want to know.<br>• <b>Emergency:</b> If no SDM is available and it's life-saving, you treat without consent.<br><br><div style='background:#f0fdf4; border-left:5px solid var(--green); padding:10px; border-radius:8px;'><b>⚠️ Exam Trap:</b> A signed consent form is <b>evidence</b> of consent, but not consent itself. If the patient changes their mind verbally after signing, the verbal refusal <b>trumps</b> the form.</div>",
    "quiz": { "q": "What is the age of majority for medical consent in Ontario?", "a": "There is no fixed age (Mature Minor doctrine applies)." }
