    "content": "Distinguishing the two depends on the time and severity.<br><br><table><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Adjustment Disorder</th><th>Major Depression (MDD)</th></tr><tr><td>Trigger</td><td>Identifiable stressor</td><td>May or may not exist</td></tr><tr><td>Timing</td><td>Within 3 months of stress</td><td>> 2 weeks</td></tr><tr><td>Criteria</td><td>Sub-threshold for MDD</td><td>Full SIGECAPS (5/9)</td></tr></table><br><div style='background:#fdf2f8; border-left:5px solid var(--pink); padding:10px; border-radius:8px;'><b>⚠️ Exam Trap:</b> Grief (bereavement) is normal. It becomes MDD only if it's persistent, causes severe functional impairment, or involves suicidality/worthlessness.</div>",
    "quiz": { "q": "What is the first-line treatment for Adjustment Disorder?", "a": "Psychotherapy (CBT or counseling)." }
